


The istream_refetch function "istream_refetch.h"

            The istream_refetch function attempts to read a
            nonblank line of printing characters from the
            standard input stream by calling istream_fetch.
              If the call to istream_fetch fails, the
            istream_refetch function returns a positive
            value, indicating an error.
              Otherwise, the call to istream_fetch succeeds;
            the string corresponding to the line is found in
            the object specified by #0, and the
            istream_refetch function returns zero.
